3 §1867.1 PBM duty; compensation; audits; contract and other requirements
4 A. PBM Duty
5 (1) A pharmacy benefit manager shall owe the pharmacy benefit
6 manager duty to any enrollee, health plan, or provider that receives pharmacy
7 benefit management services from the pharmacy benefit manager or that
8 furnishes, covers, receives, or is administered a unit of a prescription drug for
9 which the pharmacy benefit manager has provided pharmacy benefit
10 management services.
11 (a) Duty to enrollees. The pharmacy benefit manager fiduciary duty
12 owed to enrollees shall include duties of care and good faith and fair dealing.
13 The commissioner shall adopt rules and regulations defining the scope of the
14 duties owed to enrollees, including by obligating pharmacy benefit managers to
15 provide all pharmacy benefit management services related to formulary design,
16 utilization management, and grievances and appeals in a transparent manner
17 to enrollees that is consistent with the best interest of enrollees and to disclose
18 all conflicts of interest to enrollees.
19 (b) Duty to health plans. The pharmacy benefit manager duty owed to
20 health plans shall include duties of care and good faith and fair dealing. The
21 commissioner shall adopt rules and regulations defining the scope of the duties
22 owed to health plans, including by obligating pharmacy benefit managers to
23 provide transparency to health plans about amounts charged or claimed by the
24 pharmacy benefit manager in a manner that is adequate to identify all instances
25 of spread pricing and to disclose all conflicts of interest to health plans.
26 (c) Duty to providers. The pharmacy benefit manager duty owed to
27 providers shall include duties of care and good faith and fair dealing. The
28 commissioner shall adopt rules and regulations defining the scope of the duties
29 owed to providers, including by obligating pharmacy benefit managers to
